                <head>198. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>On November 6, <persName corresp="#p_AK1">Adenauer</persName> and <persName
                        corresp="#p_MG2">Mollet</persName> met in Paris in an effort to resolve the
                    remaining differences between the Federal Republic of Germany and France over
                    the proposed <gloss target="#t_EURATOM1">EURATOM</gloss> and Common Market
                    treaties. The text of the agreement which they reached was transmitted to the
                    Department in telegram 1822 from Bonn, November 10. (Department of State,
                    Central Files, 840.00/11–1056)</p>
            </div>
